Is it?  Or is the real phrase:  I couldn't care less, and then it is getting mangled into &quot;I could care less&quot;.  <br>
<br>
But &quot;I could care less&quot; about it but the one that really gets to me is people spelling coming with two M's.  <br>
<br>
It is COMING!  It is INCOMING!<br>
<br>
And then people using casted as the past tense to cast.  No, no, no!  It is:  I just cast Aego on you, not I just casted Aego on you!<br>
<br>
