<br>
And yes, I'd have to say this phrase qualifies as an idiom, especially this definiton:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>An expression conforming or appropriate to the peculiar structural form of a language; in extend use, an expression sanctioned by usage, having a sense peculiar to itself and not agreeing with the logical sense of its structural form; also, the phrase forms peculiar to a particular author.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The two examples you quoted were, respectively, a spelling mistake and incorrectly assigning a past tense suffix to a verb that doesn't use one. &quot;I could care less&quot; in its popular usage fits neatly with the definition given above. <p><table border=1>
