<br>
I believe the phrase was created by someone of the male gender.  It is obvious.  Those of us who are a part of the male gender will understand where i am coming from because we as males have traveled down this road before.  Let me explain.<br>
<br>
You ever been grazed on your testicles?  you werent hit full on in the nutsack.  Simply grazed.  But your balls react as if in pain?  You ever talk about painful experience that have to do with testicular injury, that go into great detail that it makes you cringe?  Your balls ever hurt as if in pain?  You ever see a BIG FAT UGLY STINKY girl with facial hair and drool, looking like she's lost because she cant find the closest burger stand to appease her belly?  and then your friend looks over at you and say's &quot;DUDE, i know you want her to wrap her herpetic fat vagina around your dick, dont lie&quot;.  in that instant your testicles curl up into your body as if afraid?  <br>
<br>
in all these scenario's your testicles were never in any danger. But yet they reacted and sent a signal to your brain to indicate a potential for excruciating pain.  So a &quot;near miss&quot; would still indicate or show a sense of danger worth talking about and spreading to your buddies so as to avoid the actual hit so it doesnt initiate the &quot;near miss&quot; testicular pain that would happen if they tried to avoid the actual hit.<br>
<br>
This is how i came up with theory on who created the idiom &quot;Near miss&quot;.  It only makes sense.<br>
<br>
